cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DS

This paper discusses the behavior of deep neural networks during training, specifically in relation to the width of the layers. The paper focuses on the optimization process and the Hessian matrix, which are both topics related to machine learning and optimization, falling under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of neural networks in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) applications. The paper also uses mathematical analysis and linear algebra, which are topics related to numerical analysis (cs.NE) and data structures (cs.DS).
